Previously ‘short’ and ‘comfortable’ were never found in the same sentence when describing ultra-compact crossbows but the TX Ultra 26.5 changes that – it excels in ground blind hunting and run-and-gun situations where maneuverability is critical.

Every component is designed with sniper-like accuracy and category-leading reliability. NEW 8 MM Axles and NEW X-Wide Limbs create a more stable repeatable and reliable shooting platform while the NEW ACU-X Arrow with Snap-On Nock and upgraded custom string deliver devastating long-range accuracy.

Web Item Name: Tenpoint ACUsled Rectractable Rope Cocker Sled
Web Item Description:
A portable retractable rope-cocker designed for most TenPoint Horton and Wicked Ridge crossbows including reverse-draw and acute string angle crossbows the new ACUsled reduces a crossbow’s draw weight by 50 percent and reduces the risk of inaccurate cocking that can occur with traditional rope-cockers and thus improves a shooter’s accuracy. Then the grips dovetail neatly together to form a compact unit for easy storage.

Web Item Name: TenPoint ACUrope Retractable Crossbow Rope-Cocker
Web Item Description:
The patented ACUrope is a revolutionary portable retractable crossbow rope-cocker that cocks a crossbow like traditional rope-cockers on the market today - but that’s where the comparison ends. When the shooter is finished cocking the bow the ACUrope’s draw cord completely retracts inside one of the two grips. Then the grips dovetail neatly together to form a compact unit that the hunter can conveniently slip inside a belt-mounted holster or pouch. The unit’s slender draw cords pound-for-pound 15-times stronger than steel are made of heat and abrasion resistant SPECTRA 1000 fiber.

  • Draws the bow accurately every time

Item Name: ACU-X Lighted Nock for HP Bushing 3pk
Web Item Name: TenPoint ACU-X Snap-On Lighted Crossbow Nock 3/ct
Web Item Description:
3-pack ACU-X Snap-On Lighted Crossbow Nock (Green)

The ACU-X Snap-On Lighted Nock contains a one-piece Nock/LED unit that is indexed with the vanes and press fits into the arrow’s Aluminum Bushing. Upon firing the crossbow the bowstring’s force compresses the two pieces and activates the lighted nock. Deactivate the easy on/off ACU-X Snap-On Lighted Nock by pulling the nock straight out until the light turns off. The LED light of the ACU-X Snap-On Lighted Nock system lasts for approximately twenty-four hours when activated. Use of the Bednar Perfect Puller 2.0 makes lighted nock deactivation extremely easy.

  • Easy-to-use one-piece ACU-X Snap-On Nock / LED unit – no assembly required
  • 515+ FPS approved
  • Features a Nock Retention Groove that allows the user to both hear and feel the positive engagement of the nock to the string on TenPoint rail-less crossbows
  • Bowstring activated
  • Super bright LED light provides superior arrow flight visibility
  • Easy deactivation
  • 24-hour battery life when activated (approximate)
  • Features TenPoint’s ACU-X Snap-On Nock (Only for use with TenPoint Rail-Less Crossbows)
  • Fits all TenPoint & Wicked Ridge arrows with an HP Aluminum Bushing (sold separately)
  • 3 Lighted Nocks per pack
  • Nock Weight: 27-grains

*Note: HP Aluminum Bushing and Arrow sold separately

Item Name: Tenpoint CenterPunch HPX Carbon Arrows 20'' w/ Alpha-Nock HPX .001''
Web Item Name: Tenpoint CenterPunch HPX Carbon Arrows 20'' w/ Alpha-Nock HPX .001''
Web Item Description:
NOTE: Required for use with TenPoint rail-less crossbows (TRX 515 and TX 440)

TenPoint’s Most Accurate 20-inch Arrow

Measuring 20-inches in length weighing 445-grains & featuring 15.5% FOC the Tenpoint CenterPunch HPX is spine-aligned to the odd color vane & is TenPoint’s most accurate 20″ arrow.

Each arrow is inspected for straightness to within .001” and each package is weight-grain matched within 1-grain per arrow.  Featuring a unidirectional carbon inner layer for stiffness and a woven carbon fiber outer layer for impact strength the arrow is equipped with the patented Alpha-Nock™ HPX.

The Alpha-Nock HPX features a Nock Retention Groove that snaps into the TriggerTech trigger box on the TRX 515 & TX 440 allowing the user to both hear & feel the positive engagement of the nock to the string – indicating your arrow is properly locked & loaded in the crossbow. In addition the “snap-in” design of the Nock Retention Groove eliminates the fit disadvantages & string wear associated with “snap-on” nock designs.

The Alpha-Nock HPX also features an HP Aluminum Bushing for increased strength and accuracy a deep bowstring groove a large smooth radius base and elongated ears.  The crossbow string wraps tightly around the center of the Alpha-Nock HPX resulting in straight nock travel and precision down-range accuracy while minimizing serving wear.

  • 20-inches
  • 445-grains
  • 3-inch Bohning X Vanes™
  • .001 Straightness
  • Weight-grain matched to within 1-grain per arrow.
  • Alpha-Nock HPX
  • Unidirectional carbon inner layer for stiffness and a woven carbon fiber outer layer for impact strength.

The R100 Realtree Edge Blind comfortably fits 2 hunters and has a 65" center height hub to hub 63" x 63" and floor space 49.5" x 49.5". The window configuration is on three of the four panels. The windows will contain hook and loop shoot through mesh (attached/removable) and solid fabric sewn into the blind with silent hook and loop attachments on the sides and top. The R100 contains a zippered door. Once set up you can shoot right through the mesh with a bow or a gun to stay hidden.

Item Name: Traditions Vortek StrikerFire VAPR Syn Veil Wideland No Sights .50cal
Web Item Name: Traditions Vortek StrikerFire VAPR Muzzleloader Syn Veil Wideland No Sights
Web Item Description:
The Traditions Vortek StrikerFire VAPR Muzzleloader Rifle takes in-line muzzleloaders to the next level by removing the need for an external hammer and replacing it with an internal StrikerFire System. The StrikerFire works on the same principle as modern center-fire rifle safeties. To cock the gun simply slide the striker button forward until it locks then fire. The recessed de-cocking button allows for quick and quiet de-cocking of the firearm. The gun also comes equipped with an automatic de-cocking mechanism so when the gun is opened it is automatically de-cocked. By eliminating the external hammer you get faster lock times plus the ability to mount your scope closer to the bore allows the gun to operate with less weight.

Traditions equipped the StrikerFire with some additional features. The StrikerFire is outfitted with a two-stage trigger that is set at 3 pounds and is creep free. The innovative stock design makes the rifle lighter than any other rifle in its class while still maintaining maximum strength and durability. The Strikerfire VAPR model comes with a 1:24" fast twist barrel which is designed to properly stabilize modern high-BC muzzleloading bullets.

The StrikerFire also features a Premium Burnt Bronze CeraKote finish Veil Wideland Camo stock one-piece Accelerator Breech Plug that allows you to fire both loose or pelletized powder without changing the breech plug a Dual Safety System and Speed Load System that enables easier loading and more consistent groupings. This model also includes mounted adjustable fiber optic sights.

Web Item Description: The Traditions Buckstalker XT Break Action Black Powder Rifle is a lightweight compact and maneuverable black powder rifle that combines all of the features Traditions is known for into one fantastic firearm. The Buckstalker XT 24" barrel makes it perfect for any application from shots thru dense brush to long range across a field. It comes with 3-9x40 mounted and bore sighted scope a solid aluminum ramrod and Quick-T ramrod handle. It features the Speed Load System for easy bullet starting and the Dual Safety System making it one of the safest guns available. The Buckstalker XT is also equipped with the Accelerator Breech Plug. This award winning breech plug removes in three full rotations and requires no tools! All of these great features together in one package makes the Traditions Buckstalker XT In Line Muzzleloader the best value in black powder!

Like Summit's other harnesses this model features a high-performance shock-absorbing bungee tether which minimizes slack but elongates to allow for extra travel when needed making climbing in your Summit stand even easier.

Each side of the harness has loops for lineman-style climbing when hunting from a hang-on stand. Lineman's Rope sold separately. This harness also has the back utility loop that's perfect for attaching a deer drag.

SPECIFICATIONS

  • Maximum weight limit: 300 lbs.
  • Weight: 2 lbs.
  • Sizes available:
    • Medium (for 28" to 35" waist size)
    • Large (for 35" to 46" waist size)
  • Color: Black
  • Embroidered Summit "S" on left front shoulder strap
  • High-performance bungee tether
  • Includes tether strap
